  <description><![CDATA[<p>A convenient luxury hotel offering superb value for money, the Hilton Whistler Resort &amp; Spa is a popular hotel for its great location and easy self-catering options.</p>
<h2>Prime location</h2>
<p>As one of the first hotels built in <a data-udi="umb://document/0c45d07f55a64313a6e4bc714b58b52d" href="/{localLink:umb://document/0c45d07f55a64313a6e4bc714b58b52d}" title="Whistler">Whistler</a>, the Hilton Resort &amp; Spa claims the prime position adjacent to the gondola at the bottom of Whistler mountain. You have the perfect spot to explore Blackcomb and Whistler mountains, close enough that you can almost roll out of bed and onto the slopes.</p>
<p>As you exit the hotel you are greeted with a toffee apple shop, a local coffee shop and a wide range of ski shops. There's a great selection of restaurants all within a few minutes walk of the hotel. If you are after a spot of après, you will find plenty of bars and pubs nearby.</p>
<h2>Flexible self-catering rooms</h2>
<p>With self-catering rooms available with either a full kitchen or kitchenette, the Hilton Resort &amp; Spa is ideal for those looking for great value in the Canadian Rockies. Rooms are spacious and well decorated in a modern style. The Hilton Family Combo a great choice for families, with two interconnecting rooms.</p>
<h2>Relaxation and rejuvenate</h2>
<p>If you are in need of a bit of pampering, the hotel's Taman Sari Spa offers treatments including body wraps, massages and facials, bookable locally. There is also a wellness area with outdoor pool and hot tubs.</p>]]></description>
